(54, 1, '2016-03-24 15:57:25', '2016-03-24 15:57:25', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="#">Info Form</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Auto Insurance through Mennonite Insurance\r\n\r\nAuto insurance protects you financially if you have an accident. There are many components of coverage that can make up an auto policy. Some of these coverages are state-mandated and some are optional. Each component will have coverage limits beyond which the policy will not pay.\r\n\r\nAuto insurance can have the following components:\r\n\r\n1. <strong>Bodily Injury</strong> Liability - covers other peoples injury or death which you cause with your vehicle. It does not cover injuries to you or people on your policy. Mandatory in most states.\r\n2.<strong> Property Damage</strong> Liability - covers damage you cause to someone elses property with your vehicle. Mandatory in most states.\r\n3. <strong>Uninsured and underinsured motorist</strong> - you are buying coverages #1 and #2 for the other driver, so you can recover if you are injured and the other driver has no or insufficient liability insurance. Optional in most states.\r\n4. <strong>Medical Payments</strong> - covers medical expenses to you or your passengers caused by an accident regardless of fault. It can include accidents when you are a pedestrian or bicyclist. Optional in most states.\r\n5. <strong>Comprehensive and Collision</strong> - covers property damage to your vehicle. These components will have a deductible. These coverages are not state mandated, but may be required by a lendor or leasing company.\r\n6. <strong>Miscellaneous</strong> - depending on the insurance company, coverage can be offered for rental car reimbursement, towing, or other expenses you might incur as a result of an accident. These coverages are optional.\r\n\r\nAll states require liability insurance on the cars you drive. The state mandated minimum insurance is very low. An injured persons damages can easily exhaust the minimum limits. Many people choose limits higher than the state minimums and some will purchase an umbrella policy that increases their auto (and home) liability limits by $1 million or more.\r\n\r\nWhen you write both your home and auto through us, we provide a 20% discount on your home. If you reside in Fresno, Bakersfield, Visalia or elsewhere in the service area of Personal Express Insurance, they will apply a 10% discount to their auto premium.\r\n\r\nUseful Links to state regulations in your state:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.azdot.gov/mvd/faqs/scripts/FAQsResponse.asp?Category=3&amp;Keyword=">Arizona DOT</a>\r\n<a href="http://dmv.ca.gov/vr/insurance.htm">California DMV</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.cbs.state.or.us/external/ins/publications/consumer/2085.pdf">Oregon DMV Good resource on auto insurance</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.dol.wa.gov/driverslicense/insurance.html"> Washington DOL</a></p>', 'Auto Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-24 15:57:25', '2016-03-24 15:57:25', '', 2, 'http://localhost:8080/?p=54', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(55, 1, '2016-03-24 16:22:36', '2016-03-24 16:22:36', '<a href="#">Info Form</a>\r\n<h3 class="headerSection">Mennonite Church Insurance</h3>\r\n<div class="bodySection">Church Insurance\r\n\r\nA treatise on church insurance is beyond the scope of this article. However, if one or more of these scenarios apply to your church, you should make sure you have the proper coverages in place.\r\n\r\n<strong>Does your church own property, e.g. buildings or contents?</strong> Could it easily afford to replace these if they were damaged, destroyed or stolen? If not, your church may need property insurance.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do members and non-members come to your church campus</strong> or participate in church activities? Every person who relates to your church presents a witness opportunity. However, any of these people could also be injured, and the church may be held responsible for those injuries. Your church may need general liability insurance.\r\n\r\nDoes your church have <strong>employees</strong>? The state requires workers compensation insurance.\r\n\r\nDoes the church own <strong>motor vehicles</strong>? It will need at least liability coverage for those autos.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do church members use their own vehicles for church business?</strong> Even just to run an errand? Does the church rent or borrow vehicles for youth trips? If an accident occurs, the church could be named in a lawsuit. The coverage for these accidents is known as non-owned and hired auto coverage and can be endorsed to the church auto policy or the general liability policy.\r\n\r\n<strong>Does the church let other organizations use its facilities?</strong> Do you require that your church be endorsed on the other organizations liability policy as an additional named insured? Injuries that occur on the church property will almost certainly involve the church even if another organization was in charge at the time.\r\n\r\nDoes your church rent the facilities where you worship? Does the landlord require a certificate of liability insurance?\r\n\r\n<strong>Do your pastors counsel</strong> others, even if they are not members of your church?\r\n\r\n<strong>Do your staff and volunteers supervise or teach young children?</strong> Does the church have practices and procedures in place to minimize the risk of sexual abuse? Do you think you should run <u><strong><a href="http://www.mennoniteinsurance.com/loanOptions/Extra%20Pages/Church%20Background%20Checks/">background checks?</a></strong></u><u></u>\r\n\r\nMennonite Insurance can help with these and other scenarios. We specialize in serving Mennonite, Mennonite Brethren, Brethren in Christ, and other Anabaptist churches in Arizona, California, Oregon and Washington. If you are outside our service area, we can often refer you to another Mennonite insurance company.</div>', 'Church Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '41-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-24 16:22:36', '2016-03-24 16:22:36', '', 41, 'http://localhost:8080/?p=55', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(56, 1, '2016-03-28 18:53:14', '2016-03-28 18:53:14', '<p style="text-align: justify;">[ninja_forms_modal_form id=6 text_link="Click here to fill out out form"]</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Auto Insurance through Mennonite Insurance</p>\r\nAuto insurance protects you financially if you have an accident. There are many components of coverage that can make up an auto policy. Some of these coverages are state-mandated and some are optional. Each component will have coverage limits beyond which the policy will not pay.\r\n\r\nAuto insurance can have the following components:\r\n\r\n1. <strong>Bodily Injury</strong> Liability - covers other peoples injury or death which you cause with your vehicle. It does not cover injuries to you or people on your policy. Mandatory in most states.\r\n2.<strong> Property Damage</strong> Liability - covers damage you cause to someone elses property with your vehicle. Mandatory in most states.\r\n3. <strong>Uninsured and underinsured motorist</strong> - you are buying coverages #1 and #2 for the other driver, so you can recover if you are injured and the other driver has no or insufficient liability insurance. Optional in most states.\r\n4. <strong>Medical Payments</strong> - covers medical expenses to you or your passengers caused by an accident regardless of fault. It can include accidents when you are a pedestrian or bicyclist. Optional in most states.\r\n5. <strong>Comprehensive and Collision</strong> - covers property damage to your vehicle. These components will have a deductible. These coverages are not state mandated, but may be required by a lendor or leasing company.\r\n6. <strong>Miscellaneous</strong> - depending on the insurance company, coverage can be offered for rental car reimbursement, towing, or other expenses you might incur as a result of an accident. These coverages are optional.\r\n\r\nAll states require liability insurance on the cars you drive. The state mandated minimum insurance is very low. An injured persons damages can easily exhaust the minimum limits. Many people choose limits higher than the state minimums and some will purchase an umbrella policy that increases their auto (and home) liability limits by $1 million or more.\r\n\r\nWhen you write both your home and auto through us, we provide a 20% discount on your home. If you reside in Fresno, Bakersfield, Visalia or elsewhere in the service area of Personal Express Insurance, they will apply a 10% discount to their auto premium.\r\n\r\nUseful Links to state regulations in your state:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.azdot.gov/mvd/faqs/scripts/FAQsResponse.asp?Category=3&amp;Keyword=">Arizona DOT</a>\r\n<a href="http://dmv.ca.gov/vr/insurance.htm">California DMV</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.cbs.state.or.us/external/ins/publications/consumer/2085.pdf">Oregon DMV Good resource on auto insurance</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.dol.wa.gov/driverslicense/insurance.html"> Washington DOL</a>', 'Auto Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-28 18:53:14', '2016-03-28 18:53:14', '', 2, 'http://localhost:8080/?p=56', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
