(59, 1, '2016-03-28 18:55:39', '2016-03-28 18:55:39', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>[ninja_forms_modal_form id=6 text_link="Click here to fill out out form"]</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Auto Insurance through Mennonite Insurance</p>\r\nAuto insurance protects you financially if you have an accident. There are many components of coverage that can make up an auto policy. Some of these coverages are state-mandated and some are optional. Each component will have coverage limits beyond which the policy will not pay.\r\n\r\nAuto insurance can have the following components:\r\n\r\n1. <strong>Bodily Injury</strong> Liability - covers other peoples injury or death which you cause with your vehicle. It does not cover injuries to you or people on your policy. Mandatory in most states.\r\n2.<strong> Property Damage</strong> Liability - covers damage you cause to someone elses property with your vehicle. Mandatory in most states.\r\n3. <strong>Uninsured and underinsured motorist</strong> - you are buying coverages #1 and #2 for the other driver, so you can recover if you are injured and the other driver has no or insufficient liability insurance. Optional in most states.\r\n4. <strong>Medical Payments</strong> - covers medical expenses to you or your passengers caused by an accident regardless of fault. It can include accidents when you are a pedestrian or bicyclist. Optional in most states.\r\n5. <strong>Comprehensive and Collision</strong> - covers property damage to your vehicle. These components will have a deductible. These coverages are not state mandated, but may be required by a lendor or leasing company.\r\n6. <strong>Miscellaneous</strong> - depending on the insurance company, coverage can be offered for rental car reimbursement, towing, or other expenses you might incur as a result of an accident. These coverages are optional.\r\n\r\nAll states require liability insurance on the cars you drive. The state mandated minimum insurance is very low. An injured persons damages can easily exhaust the minimum limits. Many people choose limits higher than the state minimums and some will purchase an umbrella policy that increases their auto (and home) liability limits by $1 million or more.\r\n\r\nWhen you write both your home and auto through us, we provide a 20% discount on your home. If you reside in Fresno, Bakersfield, Visalia or elsewhere in the service area of Personal Express Insurance, they will apply a 10% discount to their auto premium.\r\n\r\nUseful Links to state regulations in your state:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.azdot.gov/mvd/faqs/scripts/FAQsResponse.asp?Category=3&amp;Keyword=">Arizona DOT</a>\r\n<a href="http://dmv.ca.gov/vr/insurance.htm">California DMV</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.cbs.state.or.us/external/ins/publications/consumer/2085.pdf">Oregon DMV Good resource on auto insurance</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.dol.wa.gov/driverslicense/insurance.html"> Washington DOL</a>', 'Auto Insurance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-28 18:55:39', '2016-03-28 18:55:39', '', 2, 'http://localhost:8080/?p=59', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
